## Scenario 003 - Privilege Escalation and Persistence Through Sudo Group Membership

### Objective

Simulate an attacker who already has administrative access on a Linux host and establishes persistence by creating multiple privileged accounts.

The objective is to generate observable events related to account creation, privilege assignment, and persistence mechanisms.

---

### MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

| Technique                         | ID    |
| --------------------------------- | ----- |
| Create Account                    | T1136 |
| Account Manipulation              | T1098 |
| Valid Accounts                    | T1078 |
| Abuse Elevation Control Mechanism | T1548 |

---

### Environment

| Host     | IP        | Role         |
| -------- | --------- | ------------ |
| Ubuntu24 | 10.10.6.3 | Linux Target |
| Splunk   | 10.10.5.X | SIEM         |

---

### Initial Situation

The account:

```text
karen
```

already possessed administrative privileges through sudo.

An attacker operating under this account attempted to establish long-term persistence by creating additional privileged users.

---

### Account Creation

Ten local accounts were created.

```text
margit
godrick
rennala
radahn
rykard
morgott
mohg
malenia
maliketh
godfrey
```

Commands executed:

```bash
sudo adduser margit
sudo adduser godrick
sudo adduser rennala
sudo adduser radahn
sudo adduser rykard
sudo adduser morgott
sudo adduser mohg
sudo adduser malenia
sudo adduser maliketh
sudo adduser godfrey
```

---

### Privilege Assignment

Each account was granted administrative privileges.

```bash
sudo usermod -aG sudo margit
sudo usermod -aG sudo godrick
sudo usermod -aG sudo rennala
sudo usermod -aG sudo radahn
sudo usermod -aG sudo rykard
sudo usermod -aG sudo morgott
sudo usermod -aG sudo mohg
sudo usermod -aG sudo malenia
sudo usermod -aG sudo maliketh
sudo usermod -aG sudo godfrey
```

---

### Attack Flow

```text
Attacker (karen)
        │
        ▼
sudo adduser
        │
        ▼
Local Accounts Created
        │
        ▼
sudo usermod -aG sudo
        │
        ▼
Administrative Privileges Granted
        │
        ▼
Persistence Established
```

---

### Log Source

```text
Ubuntu24
└── /var/log/auth.log
        │
        ▼
Splunk Universal Forwarder
        │
        ▼
Index: linux
        │
        ▼
Linux Monitoring Dashboard
```

---

### Splunk Detection

Account creation:

```spl
index=linux host=vUbu24 sourcetype=linux_auth "adduser"
```

Privilege assignment:

```spl
index=linux host=vUbu24 sourcetype=linux_auth "usermod"
```

All privileged activity:

```spl
index=linux host=vUbu24 sourcetype=linux_auth "COMMAND="
| rex "COMMAND=(?<command>.*)"
```

---

### Expected Indicators

Examples of observable events:

```text
COMMAND=/usr/sbin/adduser margit
COMMAND=/usr/sbin/adduser godrick
COMMAND=/usr/sbin/adduser rennala

COMMAND=/usr/sbin/usermod -aG sudo margit
COMMAND=/usr/sbin/usermod -aG sudo godrick
COMMAND=/usr/sbin/usermod -aG sudo rennala
```

---

### Detection Outcome

The activity generated clear evidence of:

* Local account creation
* Administrative group modification
* Privileged command execution
* Persistence establishment

These actions were successfully ingested and visualized through the Linux Monitoring Dashboard in Splunk.
